ZH: 行人在人行道上穿行。
EN: Pedestrians walk on the sidewalk.
ZH: 行人应该遵守交通规则。
EN: Pedestrians should obey traffic rules.
ZH: 行人应该看红绿灯过马路。
EN: Pedestrians should wait for the traffic lights to cross the road.
ZH: 行人必须注意车辆。
EN: Pedestrians must watch out for vehicles.
ZH: 行人不能随意横穿马路。
EN: Pedestrians should not jaywalk.
ZH: 行人要确保安全通过十字路口。
EN: Pedestrians should make sure to cross intersections safely.
ZH: 行人被称为道路上最弱势的交通参与者之一。
EN: Pedestrians are considered one of the most vulnerable road users.
ZH: 行人在城市中扮演重要的角色。
EN: Pedestrians play an important role in the city.
ZH: 行人在公共交通中扮演着重要的角色。
EN: Pedestrians play a crucial role in public transportation.
ZH: 行人应该互相尊重。
EN: Pedestrians should respect each other.
ZH: 行人应该与其他交通参与者共享道路。
EN: Pedestrians should share the road with other road users.
ZH: 行人需要上下班，购物，遛狗等。
EN: Pedestrians need to commute, shop, walk dogs, etc.
ZH: 行人在雨天要特别小心。
EN: Pedestrians should be extra careful in rainy weather.
ZH: 行人应该戴上反光背心晚上步行。
EN: Pedestrians should wear reflective vests when walking at night.
ZH: 行人在夜间不宜穿黑色衣物。
EN: Pedestrians should avoid wearing dark clothes at night.
ZH: 行人应该避开繁忙的十字路口。
EN: Pedestrians should avoid busy intersections.
ZH: 行人需要注意交通信号。
EN: Pedestrians need to pay attention to traffic signals.
ZH: 行人要特别注意电动车和单车。
EN: Pedestrians should pay special attention to electric bikes and bicycles.
ZH: 行人应该帮助盲人过马路。
EN: Pedestrians should assist blind people to cross the road.
